In article <9303220604.AA16809@pizzabox.demon.co.uk> gtoal@gtoal.com
(Graham Toal) writes:
> So, is this practical, and if it is, does anyone have a good OTP generator
> for Unix?

Your suggested protocol is totally useless with OTPs.

An eavesdropper merely needs to intercept all three messages and XOR
them.

There are public-key ciphers that will allow this kind of thing, but a
one-time-pad just won't cut it.


